channel.description:
This is very easy to do, I know, don't go flaming me. Basically this is a lot better way for people that want to globally announce something for example using a yell command you can easily add this method. Anyway go to client and search for 'sendmessage' under that method add this: 

[code]	public void globalMessage(String message){
		for (Player p : PlayerHandler.players) {
			if (p == null) continue;
			Client c = (Client) p;
				c.sendMessage(message);
		}
	}
[/code]

Now to use this method it goes like this. If you are using within client class you would simply a use: 
[code]
c.globalMessage("Your message goes here");
[/code]

Simples
